I lost my senior season to a stress fracture and though I'd largely achieved my goals it was still incredibly hard.  What I've learned gradually since is that running is so much more than any race or any season and we cannot let these things which happen and make us so angry and distraught define us.  The sport is bigger than anything we will ever achieve or hope to achieve in it and it will be with you as long as you're with it.  That being said, it will take a while to feel okay about what happens and that's okay, but know that running will always be with you.
